<blockquote>
  <p>Standing on my balcony<br />
I begin to wring a poem<br />
From the sunset.<br />
‘Each year, I swallow summer whole<br />
Gulp it down<br />
And each autumn, I begin to choke’<br />
No, that’s no good, I say<br />
It’s not perfect<br />
‘I swallow summer whole<br />
And let it swill there,<br />
Filling me in the winter
And each spring,<br />
I find I am hungry again’<br />
No, not perfect.<br />
While smoke wraps around my fingers<br />
Like the suns last caresses<br />
Six swallows fly overhead<br />
And I begin to laugh.</p>
</blockquote>
